`.github/` is the repo's CI trigger point, containing only the
`workflows/` subtree. It has no direct contract of its own — everything
about behavior, environment setup, and check logic lives in
`workflows/rollup.ctx` and, beyond that, in `scripts/ci.sh` and
`rust-toolchain.toml` at the repo root. Depending on `.github/` gets a
downstream reader nothing; it's invoked by GitHub on push/PR, not
imported or called by other code.

There is nothing to couple across children since `workflows/` is the only
child, so no cross-file invariant exists at this level beyond what's
already documented there.

No intent.md exists for this directory, so there is nothing to check for
divergence.